Goal

You will:

Create a simple HTML page
Run Nginx container
Serve your custom site in browser


Step 1: Create a custom website

Inside your  VM:

mkdir mysite
cd mysite
nano index.html

Paste this inside the index.htm:

<!DOCTYPE html>
<html>
<head>
    <title>My First Docker Website</title>
</head>
<body>
    <h1>Hello from Docker 🚀</h1>
    <h2>Deployed by <user_name></h2>
</body>
</html>

Save:

Press CTRL + X
Press Y
Press Enter

Step 2: Run Nginx with your website

docker run -d \
--name my-nginx \
-p 8080:80 \
-v $(pwd):/usr/share/nginx/html \
nginx

under standing below  command does

-p 8080:80 → expose Nginx to browser
-v $(pwd):/usr/share/nginx/html → mount your folder into container

Step 3: Open in browser

http://<your-vm-ip>:8080

Result:

it shudl show you wbsite.



